    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sound example featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine. The powertrain remains robust, having undergone an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recent RMS seal replacement to ensure long-term reliability. The 6-speed G96 manual transaxle shifts with surgical precision, paired with a clutch that retains excellent bite and travel. Handling is sharpened by a factory-spec MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension, with Bilstein dampers providing superb damping control. The braking system features four-piston monobloc calipers with plenty of life left on the rotors. While the exterior displays minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain and chassis synchronization offer a pure, analog driving experience.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 10
    },
    {
